notes: nTIGER, TIGER/Line, and Census TIGER are registered trademarks of the Bureaunof the Census. The Redistricting Census 2000 TIGER/Line files are an extractnof selected geographic and cartographic information from the Census TIGERndata base.  The geographic coverage for a single TIGER/Line file is a countynor statistical equivalent entity, with the coverage area based on January 1,n2000 legal boundaries.  A complete set of Redistricting Census 2000 TIGER/Linenfiles includes all counties and statistically equivalent entities in the UnitednStates and Puerto Rico.  The Redistricting Census 2000 TIGER/Line files willnnot include files for the Island Areas. The Census TIGER data base representsna seamless national file with no overlaps or gaps between parts.  However, eachncounty-based TIGER/Line file is designed to stand alone as an independent datanset or the files can be combined to cover the whole Nation.  The RedistrictingnCensus 2000 TIGER/Line files consist of line segments representing physicalnfeatures and governmental and statistical boundaries.  The Redistricting Censusn2000 TIGER/Line files do NOT contain the ZIP Code Tabulation Areas (ZCTAs) andnthe address ranges are of approximately the same vintage as those appearing innthe 1999 TIGER/Line files.  That is, the Census Bureau is producing thenRedistricting Census 2000 TIGER/Line files in advance of the computer processingnthat will ensure that the address ranges in the TIGER/Line files agree with thenfinal Master Address File (MAF) used for tabulating Census 2000.  The files containninformation distributed over a series of record types for the spatial objects of ancounty.  There are 17 record types, including the basic data record, the shapencoordinate points, and geographic codes that can be used with appropriate softwarento prepare maps.  Other geographic information contained in the files includesnattributes such as feature identifiers/census feature class codes (CFCC) used tondifferentiate feature types, address ranges and ZIP Codes, codes for legal andnstatistical entities, latitude/longitude coordinates of linear and point features,nlandmark point features, area landmarks, key geographic features, and areanboundaries.  The Redistricting Census 2000 TIGER/Line data dictionary containsna complete list of all the fields in the 17 record types.n
